\f0\fs24 \cf0 Manage User Database\
Description: manage Chimera users and accounts within the database\
Actors: Manager, Database\
Pre-condition: Must be authentic Chimera Manager\
Triggers:\
Basic Flow: \
	1. Manager logins in to admin account and chooses the user database\
	2. The system shows a list of all Chimera users\
	3. Manager can select accounts to delete, add, suspend, or edit\
	3. If manager chooses an account to edit, the selected account is loaded  \
	4. Changes can be made to various attributes\
	5. The system updates the database and shows the changes \
Extensions:\
	1. Un-suspend account\
		1a. Manager selects un-suspend option\
		1b. The system saves the changes \
		1c. Account is now active again\
	2. Cancel changes\
		1a. After making changes to an account, manger clicks cancel button to undo\
		1b. System does no update\
